Long formShort form <p>Use the <code>build</code> subcommand by executing: Bash<pre><code>$ spice build [options] &lt;main-source-file&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p>Use the <code>build</code> command by executing: Bash<pre><code>$ spice b [options] &lt;mail-source-file&gt;
</code></pre></p>

Long formShort form <p>Use the <code>install</code> subcommand by executing: Bash<pre><code>$ spice install [options] &lt;main-source-file&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p>Use the <code>install</code> subcommand by executing: Bash<pre><code>$ spice i [options] &lt;mail-source-file&gt;
</code></pre></p>

Long formShort form <p>Use the <code>run</code> subcommand by executing: Bash<pre><code>$ spice run [options] &lt;main-source-file&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p>Use the <code>run</code> subcommand by executing: Bash<pre><code>$ spice r [options] &lt;main-source-file&gt;
</code></pre></p>

Long formShort form <p>Use the <code>test</code> subcommand by executing: Bash<pre><code>$ spice test [options] &lt;test-source-file&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p>Use the <code>test</code> subcommand by executing: Bash<pre><code>$ spice t [options] &lt;test-source-file&gt;
</code></pre></p>

Long formShort form <p>Use the <code>uninstall</code> subcommand by executing: Bash<pre><code>$ spice uninstall [options] &lt;main-source-file&gt;
</code></pre></p> <p>Use the <code>uninstall</code> subcommand by executing: Bash<pre><code>$ spice u [options] &lt;mail-source-file&gt;
</code></pre></p>

Bash<pre><code>cd build
./spice [options] &lt;input&gt;
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>type I32 alias int;
type I64 alias long;

type T int|long|short;
type TestStruct&lt;T&gt; struct {
    bool f1
    unsigned T f2
}
type TS alias TestStruct&lt;short&gt;;
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>// Attribute for the whole module
#![core.linker.flag = "-pthread"]

// ...
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>#[core.compiler.mangleName = false]
f&lt;int&gt; test(long input) {
    return input == 0 ? 123 : 456;
}

// ...
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>#[core.compiler.mangleName = false]
ext f&lt;heap byte*&gt; malloc(unsigned long);

// ...
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>#[core.compiler.alwaysEmitVTable = true]
public type A struct {
    // ...
}
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>#[core.compiler.fixedTypeId = 230]
public type A interface {
    // ...
}
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>// Use write syscall to print "Hello World!"
const string str = "Hello World!";
syscall(/* syscall no = write */ 1s, /*fd = stdout*/ 1, /* buffer */ str, len(str));
</code></pre> <p>Warning</p> <p>It is not recommended to use the syscall builtin directly. There is a std package for interacting with the OS via system calls. Please use <code>import "std/os/syscall";</code> instead.</p>

Spice<pre><code>inline p printHelloWorld() {
    printf("Hello World!");
}

f&lt;int&gt; main() {
    printHelloWorld();
}
</code></pre> <p>corresponds to:</p> Spice<pre><code>f&lt;int&gt; main() {
    printf("Hello World!");
}
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>const int THIS_IS_A_CONSTANT = 101;

f&lt;int&gt; main() {
    THIS_IS_A_CONSTANT++; // Will give a compiler error
}
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>f&lt;int&gt; main() {
    signed int signedInt = -0x567;
}
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>f&lt;int&gt; main() {
    unsigned int unsignedInt = -0x567; // Will wrap around
}
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>type TestStruct struct {
    heap int* ptr
}
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>type A struct {
    int f1
}

type B struct {
    compose A a
    int f2
}
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>// Definition
p(int, double) lambda = p(int a, double b) {
    printf("Lambda was called with %d and %f", a, b);
};
// Call
lambda(5, 3.14);
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>// Definition
f&lt;int&gt;(const String&amp;, bool) lambda = f&lt;int&gt;(const String&amp; str, bool b) {
    if (b) {
        return str.getLength();
    } else {
        return -1;
    }
};
// Call
int result = lambda(String("Hello"), true);
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>int i32 = 0b1010;
short i16 = 0b1010s;
long i64 = 0b1010l;
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>int i32 = 0xA76E;
short i16 = 0xA76Es;
long i64 = 0xA76El;
</code></pre>

Spice<pre><code>int i32 = 0o1274;
short i16 = 0o1274s;
long i64 = 0o1274l;
</code></pre>
